'''Sharmadean Reid''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MBE}} (born 28 May 1984), is a [[British Jamaican]] entrepreneur and founder of WAH Nails.
== Early life and education == Reid was born into a big Jamaican family in [[Wolverhampton]] in 1984 and graduated from [[Central Saint Martins]] in Fashion Communication and Promotion.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}
== Career == Reid started WAH in 2005 while at university as a hip hop [[zine]] focusing on the new wave of street smart feminism.<ref name=wah>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wah-nails.com/about|title=About|website=Wah Nails|access-date=2016-12-08}}</ref> The zine developed into the WAHappenings blog and WAH Power Lunches - opportunities for women to get together and discuss careers and ideas.
After graduating in 2007, Reid worked at the men's magazine ''[[Arena Homme +|Arena Homme Plus]]'' as a Sportswear Editor before moving to [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]] as an Energy Marketing Manager.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}
In June 2009, ''[[The Independent]]'' recognised Reid as one of the "15 people who will define the future of arts in Britain".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/art/features/revealed-the-15-people-who-will-define-the-future-of-arts-in-britain-1708375.html|title=Revealed: The 15 people who will define the future of arts in Britain|date=2009-06-19|newspaper=The Independent|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-12-08}}</ref> Driven by the idea of a place for women to "hang out, form friendships and build communities"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://the-dots.com/users/sharmadean-reid-91217|title=Sharmadean Reid|website=The Dots|access-date=2016-12-08}}</ref> while being able to have "whatever you wanted on your nails",<ref name=wah /> the first WAH Nails salon was opened in August 2009.
In February 2010, WAH Nails opened concessions in [[Topshop]] Oxford Circus and [[Harvey Nichols]] Dublin. WAH Nails London was launched in September 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/08/13/wah-london-s-nail-collection-is-coming-to-boots_n_7324328.html|title=WAH London's Nail Collection Is Coming To Boots|last=UK|first=Katie Jones MyDaily|date=2014-08-13|website=The Huffington Post|access-date=2016-12-08}}</ref>
In the [[2015 Birthday Honours]], Reid was awarded an [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (Member of the Order of the British Empire) for her services to the nail and beauty industry.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/beauty/people/Sharmadean-Reid-MBE/|title=Founder of WAH Nails, Sharmadean Reid, awarded MBE|newspaper=The Telegraph|access-date=2016-12-08}}</ref>
In November 2016, Reid launched her first clothing line inspired by [[Diana, Princess of Wales|Princess Diana]] and in collaboration with [[ASOS.com|ASOS]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/fashion/article/33292/1/wah-nails-sharmadean-reid-debuts-fashion-line|title=WAH Nails’ Sharmadean Reid debuts fashion line|last=Dazed|date=2016-10-10|newspaper=Dazed|access-date=2016-12-08}}</ref> In the same month WAH Nails launched an [[augmented reality]] nail application in its London store.<ref name="ES-Dec-2016">{{cite new|title=The future's nailed: virtual manicures become a reality for Londoners thanks to WAH nails|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/beauty/nails/the-futures-nailed-virtual-manicures-become-a-reality-for-londoners-thanks-to-wah-nails-a3395271.html|newspaper=Evening Standard|location=London|first=Emma| last=McCarthy|date=14 November 2016|accessdate=10 December 2016}}</ref>
